Oregon’s football team is 3-3 this season and has not lived up to expectations. Royce Freeman, however, is living up to his preseason hype. 
Freeman, who led the Pac-12 with 19 total touchdowns last season as a freshman, is among the nation's best running backs this year, and he has a chance at becoming at least a Heisman Trophy finalist. 
Here is how Freeman ranks nationally in two key categories: 
FBS RUSHING YARDS LEADERS (2015) 
1. Leonard Fournette, LSU — 1,022 
2. Tyler Ervin, San Jose State — 874 
3. Royce Freeman , Oregon — 859 
4. Ezekiel Elliott, Ohio State — 835 
5. Brian Hill, Wyoming — 797 
FBS TOTAL TOUCHDOWNS LEADERS (2015) 
1. Jeremy McNichols, Boise State — 14 
2. Corey Coleman, Baylor — 13 
3. Leonard Fournette, LSU — 12 
T4. Royce Freeman , Oregon — 11
